by: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Evaerilith</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
High Regent of Innoruuk for <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub219.ezboard.com/bnecropolis" target="top"><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">The Necropolis</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>He who makes a beast of himself rids himself from the pain of being a man</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=685950" target="top"> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">The Regent's Armory</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maelgroth>Maelgroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/03 9:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=804.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Flayer</span><hr size=1> Eventually the slaughter stopped. Corpses littered the street, here and there individual retainers of the two great houses, ocassionally piles of corpses where powerful members of the Truth Finders or the Fire Hags had made a last stand.<br>
<br>
&quot;Is it over?&quot; Chal shuddered breathlessly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hardly, though it seems the Chath'Elg'Caress have got the worst of it, despite beginning the battle with their leadership intact.&quot; Maelgroth replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;You seem disappointed.&quot; The maiden replied turning to face the masked necromancer.<br>
<br>
&quot;I had hoped the Chath'Elg'Caress would have done better against the Ragar'Golhyrr.&quot; He sighed.<br>
<br>
&quot;You have a wager on the outcome of this war?&quot; Chal chirped delighted.<br>
<br>
&quot;You could say that.&quot; Maelgroth chuckled, escorting her back towards the De'Vir manse. He looked for Kyri in the crowd, but saw nothing but the amused faces of other Teir'Dal nobles. 'Probably out looting the dead and prying secrets from the dying.' He thought to himself.<br>
<br>
Once they reached the safety of the De'Vir front gate Maelgroth reluctantly let go of Chal. &quot;I have business to attend to, but I should have it completed before the Ascension.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't take too long.&quot; Chal giggled, &quot;I can't stay out as late as I would like, after all I am representing my house.&quot;<br>
<br>
As he walked away, he chided himself for not asking whose house she belonged to. Still, he needed to concentrate. One of the dead in the street was a high ranking member of the Chath'Elg'Caress. He needed to speak with that corpse before its memories began to fade.<br>
<br>
“Well, what have you learned brother?” Maelgroth asked his brother Malingrad. He was curious to see if his scouting of the Sol’Calar manse had gone well.<br>
<br>
“Better than expected.” Malingrad grinned, he had begun the mission with the belief that Mael had sent him into an ambush, hoping to replace him with another skilled rogue named Kyri. The mission had not been nearly as dangerous as he had feared. “The secret passages remain secret.” He chuckled, “They are very few in number, no more than a dozen members including servants. I could have attended to the matter then, but I assumed you would want to deal the final blow yourself.”<br>
<br>
The rogue watched his brother carefully, for the first time since the war of houses had begun he seemed distracted. Sure, the fire for vengeance still burned like the cursed sun, but he appeared a bit preoccupied. “I heard the Ragar’Golhyrr and the Chath’elg’Caress are broken, spending their strength in a battle in front of the D’Vir manse.” He hoped to draw out his brother with the question. They were alone in the small shack in third gate where the family had grown up. His mother and sister being away from Third Gate on other business.<br>
<br>
“You were correct in that assumption.” The necromancer replied turning his gaze directly on his brother. He found his mind kept wandering back to the maiden he had encountered at the Ascension. He turned is attention back to matters at hand, there would be time to seek out a mate once this matter of vengeance was concluded. <br>
<br>
“It was quite pleasing to see our enemies destroy each other for our entertainment, I am sorry you had to miss it. Still it is for the best that we remain in the shadows for now. The Chath’elg’Caress still have their matron mother, until she has joined her family in Innoruuk’s embrace we are at risk.”<br>
<br>
“I shall begin the search immediately.” Malingrad enthused, this was the kind of work he excelled at. “Any clues on her whereabouts?” <br>
<br>
“Where do high houses go when they fall brother?”<br>
<br>
“That’s too perfect!” Mal laughed, rising from the table and heading out into the darkness. Finding a matron mother hiding out in Third Gate would be about as difficult as picking a drunken troll’s pocket, and about as dangerous.<br>
<br>
After his brother had swaggered out of the shack, Maelgroth strode purposefully towards the back of the shack, pulling aside a rotted curtain that served as a divider, he looked down upon the mutilated corpse of a Teir’Dal noble.<br>
<br>
Energy crept from the necromancer’s outstretched hand, glistening tendrils of eldritch power, which caressed the corpse lovingly. After a moment the corpse began to twitch.<br>
<br>
“Tell me more of you plans.” Maelgroth said conversationally.<br>
<br>
With a bubbling cough the corpse began to wheeze the secrets of the Chat’elg’Caress.<br>
