<br>
“Tell me of the battle, was there much blood? By Innoruuks Curse I wish I could have seen those houses destroying each other!” She shouted.<br>
<br>
“Quiet, we must still be cautious.” Mael hissed, hurriedly closing the door. The ancient crone was in one of the most agitated states he had ever seen her in. Madness gleamed in her fevered eyes like heat radiated from hot coals. <br>
<br>
He examined the room carefully. All was as it should be. <br>
<br>
“Its true both houses have spent their strength in the street outside of the D’Vir manse.” The necromancer began.<br>
<br>
