<br>
“I understand, your sister and I shall deal with the dregs of the Ragar Golhyrr.” Naelaelayle growled.<br>
<br>
Maelgroth looked at his mother carefully, surprised that she would offer to take such a direct hand, having orchestrated much of this war from the shadows. <br>
<br>
“Malingrad should also be available to help, he should have finished his task in Third Gate by now.”<br>
<br>
“What do you mean?” His mother queried, already she was sharpening her knives, they made an evil hiss as they stroked the whetstone. <br>
<br>
“He is looking for the Fire Hag matron, rumor has it she has fled to Third Gate, I shall finish her myself.”<br>
<br>
“I suppose we should get moving then.” Naelaelayle grinned, the knives disappearing into her robe with a flourish.<br>
<br>
As the two made their way from the League manor neither noticed the figure shadowing them from a distance.<br>
